eanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Malachy, Kieran, Peadar.","Irish (Galway): variant of   Noon  ."]}]},{"name":"Edmund","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old English personal name derived from <i>ēad</i> ‘prosperity, riches’ + <i>mund</i> ‘protector’. It was borne by several early royal and saintly figures, including a 9th-century king of East Anglia killed by invading Danes, allegedly for his adherence to Christianity. In the 16th and 17th centuries, there was a good deal of interchange between <i>Edmund</i> and <i>Edward</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Edmund Noon was born about 1349, in Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, his father, Edmund Noon, was 27 and his mother, Mrs. Edmond Noon, was 27. He had at least 1 daughter with Isabel Visdelou."},"et":{"Abt 1349–Deceased":"umbes 1349–Surnud","1349–Male":"1349–Surnud","1350–1407":"1350–1407","1387–1406":"1387–1406","1323–Male":"1323–Surnud","1323–Female":"1323–Surnud","1349":"1349","1323":"1323","1387":"1387","1350":"1350","1407":"1407","1406":"1406","Abt 1349":"umbes 1349","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1349–Deceased":"noin 1349–Kuollut","1349–Male":"1349–Kuollut","1350–1407":"1350–1407","1387–1406":"1387–1406","1323–Male":"1323–Kuollut","1323–Female":"1323–Kuollut","1349":"1349","1323":"1323","1387":"1387","1350":"1350","1407":"1407","1406":"1406","Abt 1349":"noin 1349","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1349–Deceased":"environ 1349–Décédé","1349–Male":"1349–Décédé","1350–1407":"1350–1407","1387–1406":"1387–1406","1323–Male":"1323–Décédé","1323–Female":"1323–Décédée","1349":"1349","1323":"1323","1387":"1387","1350":"1350","1407":"1407","1406":"1406","Abt 1349":"environ 1349","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Edmund Noon 